messages.message:
Team,
While coordinating the release-22.01.0, i came across cypress tests that have been failing for over 2 months. Its hard to pinpoint what commit caused failure since logs for old jenkins pipeline are not availble.

I was able to quickly investigate, and looks like the tests related to ML studio are failing. Can the authors/owners PTAL and cherry-pick the fix as well? Thanks.
Logs with test failures: https://jenkins.instabase.com/job/cypress-tests/2515/consoleFull

Tagging related folks: @lydia [ML studio], @Wilson, @Serena [authors with commit in the relevant files like `webserver/shared/src/js/webpacked/apps/src/ml-studio/__e2e__/model_project_creation/model-create-extraction-project.spec.js`]
We are in progress on fixing the ML Studio Cypress tests, and I have an upcoming cherry-pick with a few changes
FYI we are not using Cypress tests to block deployments since they have never been reliably green
